The paper deals with the analysis of social networks and their community structure, which falls under the scope of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing). The paper also discusses the core-periphery structure of the network, which is a topic of interest in cs.SOC (Computational Social Science). The algorithm used for computing the core-periphery decomposition involves iterative removal of nodes, which is a technique used in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper presents explicit results and observational results, which are related to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
